   5:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   * @brief   DAC HAL module driver.
   6:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *         This file provides firmware functions to manage the following
   7:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *         functionalities of the Digital to Analog Converter (DAC) peripheral:
   8:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *           + Initialization and de-initialization functions
   9:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *           + IO operation functions
  10:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *           + Peripheral Control functions
  11:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *           + Peripheral State and Errors functions
  12:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *
  13:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   *
  14:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   @verbatim
  15:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   ==============================================================================
  16:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****                       ##### DAC Peripheral features #####
  17:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   ==============================================================================
  18:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     [..]
  19:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       *** DAC Channels ***
  20:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       ====================
  21:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     [..]
  22:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     STM32H7 devices integrate two 12-bit Digital Analog Converters
  23:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  24:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     The 2 converters (i.e. channel1 & channel2)
  25:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     can be used independently or simultaneously (dual mode):
  26:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) DAC channel1 with DAC_OUT1 (PA4) as output or connected to on-chip
  27:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           peripherals (ex. OPAMPs, comparators).
  28:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) DAC channel2 with DAC_OUT2 (PA5) as output or connected to on-chip
  29:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           peripherals (ex. OPAMPs, comparators).
  30:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\simon\AppData\Local\Temp\ccm9MwZO.s 			page 2


  31:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       *** DAC Triggers ***
  32:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       ====================
  33:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     [..]
  34:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     Digital to Analog conversion can be non-triggered using DAC_TRIGGER_NONE
  35:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     and DAC_OUT1/DAC_OUT2 is available once writing to DHRx register.
  36:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     [..]
  37:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     Digital to Analog conversion can be triggered by:
  38:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) External event: EXTI Line 9 (any GPIOx_PIN_9) using DAC_TRIGGER_EXT_IT9.
  39:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           The used pin (GPIOx_PIN_9) must be configured in input mode.
  40:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  41:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) Timers TRGO: TIM1, TIM2, TIM4, TIM5, TIM6, TIM7, TIM8, TIM15, TIM23 and TIM24
  42:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           (DAC_TRIGGER_T1_TRGO, DAC_TRIGGER_T2_TRGO...)
  43:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  44:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) Low Power Timers TRGO: LPTIM1, LPTIM2 and LPTIM3
  45:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           (DAC_TRIGGER_LPTIM1_OUT, DAC_TRIGGER_LPTIM2_OUT)
  46:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  47:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) High Resolution Timer TRGO: HRTIM1
  48:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           (DAC_TRIGGER_HR1_TRGO1, DAC_TRIGGER_HR1_TRGO2)
  49:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  50:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) Software using DAC_TRIGGER_SOFTWARE
  51:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       *** DAC Buffer mode feature ***
  52:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       ===============================
  53:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       [..]
  54:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Each DAC channel integrates an output buffer that can be used to
  55:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       reduce the output impedance, and to drive external loads directly
  56:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       without having to add an external operational amplifier.
  57:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       To enable, the output buffer use
  58:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       sConfig.DAC_OutputBuffer = DAC_OUTPUTBUFFER_ENABLE;
  59:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       [..]
  60:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (@) Refer to the device datasheet for more details about output
  61:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           impedance value with and without output buffer.
  62:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  63:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       *** DAC connect feature ***
  64:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       ===============================
  65:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       [..]
  66:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Each DAC channel can be connected internally.
  67:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       To connect, use
  68:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       sConfig.DAC_ConnectOnChipPeripheral = DAC_CHIPCONNECT_INTERNAL;
  69:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       or
  70:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       sConfig.DAC_ConnectOnChipPeripheral = DAC_CHIPCONNECT_BOTH;
  71:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  72:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       *** GPIO configurations guidelines ***
  73:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       =====================
  74:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       [..]
  75:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       When a DAC channel is used (ex channel1 on PA4) and the other is not
  76:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (ex channel2 on PA5 is configured in Analog and disabled).
  77:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Channel1 may disturb channel2 as coupling effect.
  78:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Note that there is no coupling on channel2 as soon as channel2 is turned on.
  79:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Coupling on adjacent channel could be avoided as follows:
  80:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       when unused PA5 is configured as INPUT PULL-UP or DOWN.
  81:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       PA5 is configured in ANALOG just before it is turned on.
  82:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  83:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       *** DAC Sample and Hold feature ***
  84:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       ========================
  85:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       [..]
  86:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       For each converter, 2 modes are supported: normal mode and
  87:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       "sample and hold" mode (i.e. low power mode).
ARM GAS  C:\Users\simon\AppData\Local\Temp\ccm9MwZO.s 			page 3


  88:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       In the sample and hold mode, the DAC core converts data, then holds the
  89:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       converted voltage on a capacitor. When not converting, the DAC cores and
  90:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       buffer are completely turned off between samples and the DAC output is
  91:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       tri-stated, therefore  reducing the overall power consumption. A new
  92:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       stabilization period is needed before each new conversion.
  93:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  94:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       The sample and hold allow setting internal or external voltage @
  95:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       low power consumption cost (output value can be at any given rate either
  96:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       by CPU or DMA).
  97:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
  98:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       The Sample and hold block and registers uses either LSI & run in
  99:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       several power modes: run mode, sleep mode, low power run, low power sleep
 100:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       mode & stop1 mode.
 101:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 102:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Low power stop1 mode allows only static conversion.
 103:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 104:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       To enable Sample and Hold mode
 105:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Enable LSI using HAL_RCC_OscConfig with RCC_OSCILLATORTYPE_LSI &
 106:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       RCC_LSI_ON parameters.
 107:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 108:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       Use DAC_InitStructure.DAC_SampleAndHold = DAC_SAMPLEANDHOLD_ENABLE;
 109:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****          & DAC_ChannelConfTypeDef.DAC_SampleAndHoldConfig.DAC_SampleTime,
 110:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****            DAC_HoldTime & DAC_RefreshTime;
 111:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 112:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        *** DAC calibration feature ***
 113:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        ===================================
 114:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       [..]
 115:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (#)  The 2 converters (channel1 & channel2) provide calibration capabilities.
 116:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (++) Calibration aims at correcting some offset of output buffer.
 117:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (++) The DAC uses either factory calibration settings OR user defined
 118:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****            calibration (trimming) settings (i.e. trimming mode).
 119:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (++) The user defined settings can be figured out using self calibration
 120:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****            handled by HAL_DACEx_SelfCalibrate.
 121:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (++) HAL_DACEx_SelfCalibrate:
 122:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (+++) Runs automatically the calibration.
 123:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (+++) Enables the user trimming mode
 124:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (+++) Updates a structure with trimming values with fresh calibration
 125:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****             results.
 126:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****             The user may store the calibration results for larger
 127:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****             (ex monitoring the trimming as a function of temperature
 128:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****             for instance)
 129:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 130:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        *** DAC wave generation feature ***
 131:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        ===================================
 132:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 133:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        Both DAC channels can be used to generate
 134:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****          (#) Noise wave
 135:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****          (#) Triangle wave
 136:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 137:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        *** DAC data format ***
 138:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        =======================
 139:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 140:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        The DAC data format can be:
 141:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****          (#) 8-bit right alignment using DAC_ALIGN_8B_R
 142:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****          (#) 12-bit left alignment using DAC_ALIGN_12B_L
 143:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****          (#) 12-bit right alignment using DAC_ALIGN_12B_R
 144:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\simon\AppData\Local\Temp\ccm9MwZO.s 			page 4


 145:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        *** DAC data value to voltage correspondence ***
 146:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        ================================================
 147:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 148:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        The analog output voltage on each DAC channel pin is determined
 149:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        by the following equation:
 150:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 151:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        DAC_OUTx = VREF+ * DOR / 4095
 152:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (+) with  DOR is the Data Output Register
 153:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 154:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****           VREF+ is the input voltage reference (refer to the device datasheet)
 155:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 156:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****         e.g. To set DAC_OUT1 to 0.7V, use
 157:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        (+) Assuming that VREF+ = 3.3V, DAC_OUT1 = (3.3 * 868) / 4095 = 0.7V
 158:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 159:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        *** DMA requests ***
 160:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        =====================
 161:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        [..]
 162:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        A DMA request can be generated when an external trigger (but not a software trigger)
 163:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        occurs if DMA requests are enabled using HAL_DAC_Start_DMA().
 164:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****        DMA requests are mapped as following:
 165:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) DAC channel1: mapped on DMA_REQUEST_DAC1_CH1
 166:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****       (#) DAC channel2: mapped on DMA_REQUEST_DAC1_CH2
 167:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 168:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****      [..]
 169:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****     (@) For Dual mode and specific signal (Triangle and noise) generation please
 170:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****         refer to Extended Features Driver description
 171:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 172:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****                       ##### How to use this driver #####
 173:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dac.c ****   ==============================================================================
